		<td><b>Coleco Tabletop Arcade DIY Perma Power</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Today I was doing some browsing looking for an answer to a DIY Perma Power for my Coleco Tabletop Arcade machines.<br /><br />The mini arcades run off of 4 C-cell batteries, 4 x 1.5v.<br /><br />The Coleco Perma Power Adaptor is 9v.<br /><br />Does this mean the fake C cells with the Perma Power have resistors in them to reduce the voltage or can the Coleco Tabletop Arcade machines run off of 9v?<br /><br />I have a 9v power supply and can easily make some fake C-cells, I just worry aboot putting 9v to them wihout checking first, this is not something I want to fry.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


